    <h2>Evaluation Questions</h2>
    <dl>
        <dt>URL of the Website:</dt>
        <dd><a href="https://www.theminimalists.com/" target="_blank">https://www.theminimalists.com/</a></dd>

        <dt>Name of the Website:</dt>
        <dd>The Minimalists Blog</dd>

        <dt>Target Audience:</dt>
        <dd>The Minimalists Blog is designed for individuals interested in minimalism and simplifying their lives. This blog includes audiences ranging from young adults to professionals seeking a minimalistic lifestyle.</dd>

        <dt>Organization of the Site:</dt>
        <dd>The site is organized into sections such as blog posts, books, podcasts, and documentaries. There is a navigation bar at the top to make it easier to access each category.</dd>

        <dt>CRAP Design Principle Used:</dt>
        <dd>The site uses **Repetition**, maintaining a consistent color scheme of black, white, and gray.</dd>

        <dt>Accessibility Audit Score:</dt>
        <dd>The audit score, according to the Accessibility Checker, is 95 out of 100.</dd>

        <dt>Site Effectiveness:</dt>
        <dd>The site is effective because it provides easy access to content like blog posts and podcasts, making it simpler for users to find what they're interested in.</dd>

        <dt>Site Efficiency:</dt>
        <dd>Users can navigate the site easily due to its simple and well-organized layout.</dd>

        <dt>Engagement:</dt>
        <dd>The site is easy to use with a clean and distraction-free layout that matches the theme of minimalism.</dd>

        <dt>Recommendation for Improvement:</dt>
        <dd>Adding alt text to some images would enhance accessibility, making it easier for visually impaired users to navigate the site.</dd>
    </dl>
